# Static HTML parity (optional)

This repo is **Next.js-first**. If you add or sync a separate `html/` export:

- Treat the **Next.js page as source of truth** for structure and content.
- **No** React/Next-specific code in HTML (no hooks, no `next/image` in static export — use plain `<img>` where needed).
- Next uses **`@phosphor-icons/react`** for icons; in HTML use **inline SVG or images** that match visually — not the npm package.
- Preserve **class naming** and section order so CSS and documentation stay consistent.
- Document any **intentional differences** (e.g. build-time vs static assets).

If the project has no HTML files, ignore this rule.
